Describe a time when it was important for you to tell a friend the truth
- who your friend is
- what the truth was
- what your friend's reaction was
- explain why you think it was important to tell your friend the truth

I’d like to talk about a time when I had to tell my best friend a difficult truth, which turned out to be very important. This happened about two years ago when I was in my second year at university.

At the time, I had a very close friend named Amy, and we used to share almost everything with each other. She had been in a relationship with her boyfriend for over two years, and she was deeply in love with him. I had met him a few times, and he seemed like a decent person, so I never suspected anything was wrong.

However, one day, while I was at a café with some friends, I unexpectedly saw him with another girl. From the way they behaved, it was quite clear that they were romantically involved. When he noticed me, he quickly left, and later he texted me, asking me not to tell Amy. He even promised that he would end things with the other girl if I kept it a secret.

I was in a real dilemma for a few days because I knew that telling Amy the truth would hurt her deeply, but at the same time, I felt that she deserved to know. In the end, I decided to be honest with her.

When I told her, she was completely shocked and speechless at first. Then she broke down in tears and was absolutely devastated. Shortly after that, she decided to end the relationship and cut off all contact with him.

Although it was a painful experience, I believe it was the right decision. I supported her as much as I could, and over time, she managed to move on. Now she is in a much healthier relationship and seems genuinely happy. Looking back, I’m glad I chose honesty, because it ultimately helped her avoid a much worse situation.
